{
  "texts": [
    "Text-to-SQL.",
    "Text-to-SQL is one of the most popular approaches for enabling natural language interfaces (NL) to databases.",
    "It consists of converting NL questions into valid SQL queries, where the result of the query is a set of tuples that answer the question.",
    "The advent of LLMs has facilitated the development of complex architectures, such as LLM chains and agentic flows, which have significantly enhanced the efficacy of Text-to-SQL systems (Tai et al., 2023; Li et al., 2024c; Gao et al., 2023; Pourreza and Rafiei, 2023).",
    "Our work employs such architectures to facilitate the automatic generation of insights from databases via automatically generated SQL queries."
  ]
}